EMPIRE BRICK & SUPPLY COMPANY, Libelant-Appellee, v. Steam Tug BRONX, Her Engines, etc.; Red Star Towing & Transportation Company, Claimant-Appellant; Red Star Towing & Transportation Company, Respondent-Appellant. Circuit Court of Appeals, Second Circuit. February 20, 1928. No. 140. Burlingham, Veeder, Masten & Fearey, of New York City (Chauncey I. Clark and Eugene Underwood, Jr., both of New York City, of counsel), for appellant. Alexander & Ash, of New York City (Peter Alexander, of New York City, of counsel), for appellee.

Before MANTON, L. HAND, and AUGUSTUS N. HAND, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Decree (14F.[2d] 482) affirmed, with costs.
